    Description

    Poor artist Jack and rich debutante Rose fall in love with each other while aboard the unsinkable Titanic. However, the trip takes a turn for the worse when the ship hits an iceberg.
    Release date: December 19, 1997 (USA)
    Director: James Cameron
    Awards: Academy Award for Best Picture See more
    Running time: 3h 15m
    Featured song: My Heart Will Go On
    Budget: $200 million
    Distributed by: 20th Century Studios, Paramount Pictures, Paramount Home Entertainment
